  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5864",
  "title": "Extra client-side call being made when navigating to Algolia page (Next 13, pages dir)",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\r\n\r\nWhen using the [boilerplate code](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/tree/master/examples/react/next), navigating from a simple page to a page using InstantSearch, unwanted Algolia requests appear in the network tab in the browser:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1611\" alt=\"Scherm­afbeelding 2023-09-22 om 16 51 13\" src=\"https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/110387333/942e8d50-d9fb-4529-988e-9b2dda87fca2\">\r\n\r\n**In my older projects where I'm using NextJS 12, this issue does not occur. The page simply loads without a client-side call to algolia.**\r\n\r\n\r\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. From the homepage, click on the \"Go to algolia page\" link\r\n2. Notice how a new Algolia request appears in the network tab, as soon as the Algolia page loads\r\n\r\n### Live reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/focused-hoover-z58yzs?file=%2Fpages%2Fsearch.tsx%3A21%2C10-21%2C15\r\n\r\n### 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo client-side algolia call when switching between pages.\r\n\r\n### Package version\r\n\r\ninstantsearch 7.1.0, next 13.5.1\r\n\r\n### Operating system\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
